us Christ.','1 Peter 2:5',NULL,1,NULL,10,'I present myself as a living sacrifice, Help me life in the power of your grace today JESUS',NULL),(362,'Daily Attitude of my Heart - Focus','May I not seek my own good, but that of my neighbor.','1 Corinthians 10:24',NULL,2,NULL,10,NULL,NULL),(363,'Daily Attitude of my Heart - Obey','If I am self-seeking and do not obey YOUR truth, but obey unrighteousness, there will be wrath and fury.','Romans 2:8',NULL,3,NULL,10,NULL,NULL),(364,'Daily Attitude of my Heart - Thoughts','I will not be conformed to this world, but I will be transformed by the renewing of my mind, so that I may prove YOUR good, acceptable & perfect will.','Romans 12:2','Take thoughts & feelings captive.',4,NULL,10,NULL,NULL),(365,'My Father in Heaven','Like the prodical son, sharpen my senses so if I fail I will always head back to YOU Heavenly Father.','Lk 15:17',NULL,5,NULL,10,'teach me to live in the perfect father child relationship with you.',NULL),(366,'I exalt & glorify YOUR holy Name','El Roi was first revealed in the Bible by Hagar. She was Sarah\'s handmaiden, who became pregnant with Abraham\'s child so, in their minds, they could fulfill the promise of God. Soon after the child was conceived, things became very difficult between Sarah and her. So much so, that Hagar fled out into the wilderness. Friendless, homeless, pregnant, not knowing what would become of her, she laid down by a fountain in the wilderness. There, an angel appeared to her to give her comfort and to speak of God\'s grace and mercy. Genesis 16:13 says: \"And she called the name of the LORD that spake unto her, Thou God seest me: for she said, Have I also here looked after him that seeth me?\" Did you know that God sees you right now? God knows your very thoughts. His eye is on the sparrow and I know He watches me.\n\nThe name ascribed to God by Hagar, alone and desperate in the wilderness after being driven out by Sarah (Genesis 16:1-14). When Hagar met the Angel of the Lord, she realized she had seen God Himself in a theophany. She also realized that El Roi saw her in her distress and testified that He is a God who lives and sees all.','Genesis 16:13; Genesis 16:1-16; Psalm 33:18-19',NULL,6,NULL,10,'YOU are: EL ROI [el-roh-ee]: \"God of Seeing\"',NULL),(367,'YOUR Nature','For YOU said to Moses, \"I will have mercy on whom I have mercy, & I will have compassion on whom I have compassion.\" Please choose to have mercy and compassion on me!','Rom 9:15',NULL,7,NULL,10,'I worship because YOU are: Merciful',NULL),(368,'Scripture reading',NULL,'Psalms',NULL,8,NULL,10,'Read 1 Chapter in the Psalms',NULL),(369,'Yeild to YOU','YOUR Kingdom come (act of waiting & longing for my real home), YOUR will, (timing & desire) be done on earth & in my life as it is in Heaven.','Mat 6:10',NULL,9,NULL,10,'Am I pushing forward in my life on my own or letting YOU take the lead and set the pace?',NULL),(370,'Wait on YOU','YOU are the everlasting God, the Creator of the ends of the earth. YOU do not faint or grow weary; YOUR understanding is unsearchable. YOU give power to me when I am faint, & when I have no might YOU increase my strength. Even youths shall faint & be weary, & young men shall fall exhausted; but if I wait for YOU, YOU will renew my strength; I shall mount up with wings like eagles; I will run & not be weary; I will walk & not faint.','Isaiah 40:28-31',NULL,10,NULL,10,'I am waiting & consciously pausing so YOU can take the lead today.',NULL),(371,'Recognize my sin & idoltry','For even though they knew God, they did not honor Him as God or give thanks, but they became futile in their speculations, and their foolish heart was darkened. Professing to be wise, they became fools, and exchanged the glory of the incorruptible God for an image in the form of corruptible man and of birds and four-footed animals and crawling creatures.','Romans 1:21-32',NULL,11,NULL,10,'Aaron bows to their demands, fashioning for them a golden statue of a calf, and they say, “This is your god, O Israel, who brought you up from the land of Egypt” (Exodus 32:4). We still don’t know which God they’re talking about, but Aaron makes it clear right away.',NULL),(372,'Recognize & replace','Put on: NOT EASILY PROVOKED.  A person’s wisdom yields patience; it is to one’s glory to overlook an offense. \nPs 119 Love the Sccripture, not easily offended.','Proverbs 19:11','Help me feel what hurts YOUR heart more than feeling bad for the consequences of my sin on myself.',12,NULL,10,'Put off: EASILY IRRITATED   Love does not dishonor others, it is not self-seeking, it is not easily angered, it keeps no record of wrongs. 1 Cor 13:5',NULL),(373,'Repent','The fear of the Lord is a fountain of life, that I may turn away from the snares of death.','Proverbs 14:27 ESV','Then Peter came to Jesus and asked, “Lord, how many times shall I forgive my brother or sister who sins against me? Up to seven times?” Jesus answered, “I tell you, not seven times, but seventy-seven times.  Matthew 18:21-22',13,NULL,10,'I choose by my free will to turn from any disobedience You have shown me.',NULL),(374,'Release','Good people pass away; the godly often die before their time. But no one seems to care or wonder why. No one seems to understand that God is protecting them from the evil to come. For those who follow godly paths will rest in peace when they die.','Isaiah 57:1-2 NLT',NULL,14,NULL,10,'I will fall like a just man seven times (over & over), & I will rise up again.  Pro 24:16a',NULL),(375,'Scripture reading',NULL,'Proverbs',NULL,15,NULL,10,'Read 1 Chapter in the Proverbs',NULL),(376,'Pray for One Another','1 Samuel 23 Moreover, as for me, far be it from me that I should sin against the LORD by ceasing to pray for you, and I will instruct you in the good and the right way.  24Only fear the LORD and serve him faithfully with all your heart. For consider what great things he has done for you.  25But if you still do wickedly, you shall be swept away, both you and your king.','Hebrews 10:25','Help me be encouraging to others through fellowship with others.',16,NULL,10,'Let us not give up meeting together, as some are in the habit of doing, but let us encourage one another.',NULL),(377,'Pray for salvation of others','YOU desire all people to be saved & to come to the knowledge of the truth.','1 Tim 2:4',NULL,17,NULL,10,NULL,NULL),(378,'Spouse',NULL,'Ps 90:17',NULL,18,NULL,10,'Favor -May YOUR favor rest on us, establish the work of our hands.',NULL),(379,'Kids in my life (current or future).','For my children help them find YOUR FORGIVNESS -If we confess our sins, YOU are faithful and just and will forgive us our sins and purify us from all unrighteousness.','1 Jh 1:9',NULL,19,NULL,10,'For all the kids, may they love YOU intimately & serve YOU faithfully all the days of their lives. Help me to be an example of YOU to them. Provide for each a godly spouse that draws them up closer to YOU. Help me see all the good in each one daily & encourage them accordingly being their biggest cheerleader. Thanks for the miscarried that are in Heaven looking forward to us all being together in eternity.',NULL),(380,'Pray for:','Honor your father and mother - which is the first commandment with a promise - so that it may go well with you and that you may enjoy long life on the earth(this does not just speak of the years of your life but the life of your years).','Eph 6:2-3','goughs, obeys, scovils, Thatcher, Fariss',20,NULL,10,'parents',NULL),(381,'Scripture reading',NULL,'OT',NULL,21,NULL,10,'Read 1 Chapter in the OT',NULL),(382,'Personal -Blessings','And whatever I ask in prayer, I will receive, if I have faith.','Matthew 21:22',NULL,22,NULL,10,'Give me today my daily bread.',NULL),(383,'Personal -specific issues','If I confess my sins to others and pray for them, then I may be healed. The prayer of a righteous man is powerful and effective.','James 5:16','I would like to cast on YOU now the following issues that I personally need YOU to deal with in my day today: 1 Pet 5:6-10',23,NULL,10,'humility leads',NULL),(384,'Personal -$$','Will man rob God? Yet you are robbing me. But you say, ‘How have we robbed you?’ In your tithes and contributions. You are cursed with a curse, for you are robbing me, the whole nation of you. Bring the full tithe into the storehouse, that there may be food in my house. And thereby put me to the test, says the Lord of hosts, if I will not open the windows of heaven for you and pour down for you a blessing until there is no more need. I will rebuke the devourer for you, so that it will not destroy the fruits of your soil, and your vine in the field shall not fail to bear, says the Lord of hosts. Then all nations will call you blessed, for you will be a land of delight, says the Lord of hosts.','Malachi 3:8-12',NULL,24,NULL,10,'Money exerts a certain control over us because it seems to hold out so much (false) promise of happiness. It whispers with great force, \"Think and act so as to get into a position to enjoy my benefits.\" This may include stealing, borrowing, or working. Money promises happiness, and we serve it by believing the promise and walking by that faith.\". -John Piper',NULL),(385,'Personal -power of my words','We all stumble in many ways. Anyone who is never at fault in what they say is perfect, able to keep their whole body in check.','James 3:2','Let no corrupting talk come out of your mouths, but only such as is good for building up, as fits the occasion, that it may give grace to those who hear. Eph. 4:29',25,NULL,10,'If he have faith, the believer cannot be restrained. He betrays himself. He breaks out. He confesses and teaches this gospel to the people at the risk of life itself. Martin Luther',NULL),(386,'Personal -Who am I?','Therefore, since I have been justified by faith, I have peace with YOU through my Lord Jesus Christ.','Rom 5:1','Remind me WHO I AM because of YOU JESUS:',26,NULL,10,'I am justified',NULL),(387,'My Life Purpose','And I know that if I love (obey) YOU, all things will work together for my good,  YOU have called me according to YOUR purpose. I must listen to your calling and obey, and if I do then all things will work together for my good.','Romans 8:28','What is my life vision/missions statement?',27,NULL,10,'user needs to write their here.',NULL),(388,'Thanks','I give thanks to YOU, for YOU are good, for YOUR steadfast love endures forever! Let those YOU redeemed say so, whom YOU have redeemed from trouble.','Ps 107:1',NULL,28,NULL,10,NULL,NULL),(389,'Scripture reading',NULL,'NT',NULL,29,NULL,10,'Read 1 Chapter in the NT',NULL),(390,'Warfare','Show me any enemy strongholds(sould wounds+lies) that are in my life and cast them down to utter destruction in JESUS name.','2 Timothy 1:12','May I not face tempation today and deliver me from the enemy that seeks to lie to me and get me to cooperate with the killing, stealing and destroying of everything good YOU desire to bring to my life.',30,NULL,10,'I am not ashamed, for I know whom I have believed, and I am convinced that YOU are able to guard until that Day what has been entrusted to me.',NULL),(391,'Armor On!','Today I choose to put on the complete armor of God, so that I will be able to successfully resist and stand my ground against any enemy advance today, and having done everything that today demands, to stand firm in place, fully prepared, immovable (my shield interlocked with those of the support network around me), victorious!','Luke 10:19','YOU have given me authority to tread on serpents and scorpions, and over all the power of the enemy, and nothing shall hurt me.',31,NULL,10,'Put on the armor of God.',NULL),(392,'Journal',NULL,NULL,NULL,32,NULL,10,'Journal what You said to me today:',NULL),(393,'Benidiction for my day','And let YOUR peace rule in my heart, to which indeed I was called in one body & I am thankful. Let YOUR word dwell in me richly, teaching & admonishing others in all wisdom, singing psalms, hymns & spiritual songs, with thankfulness in my heart to YOU. And whatever I do, in word or deed, I will do everything in YOUR name Lord Jesus, giving thanks to God the FATHER through YOU.','Col 3:15-17',NULL,33,NULL,10,NULL,NULL),(394,'Music with meaning.','Sing to YOU, sing praises to YOU; I will tell of all YOUR wondrous works!','Psalm 105:2',NULL,34,NULL,10,NULL,'https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLZdpE0NYhNb8oTRuuAgPt6OG0SuWcMZUK'),(395,'Pray for specific people.',NULL,NULL,'Customer user input will soon be available here.',35,NULL,10,'Who would you have me pray for right now? (fill names in below)',NULL),(396,'Forgivness','Forgive my sins in the same way & to the same degree as I forgive those that I feel have wronged and hurt me.',NULL,NULL,36,NULL,10,NULL,NULL),(397,'My List',NULL,NULL,NULL,37,NULL,10,'This will be a list of people I am praying for.',NULL),(398,'Worship & Praise -YOUR Name',NULL,'Matthew 6:9',NULL,38,NULL,10,'I exalt & glorify YOUR holy Name:',NULL),(399,'Replace my way with YOUR way, I receive:',NULL,NULL,'Custom user input will soon be available here.',39,NULL,10,NULL,NULL),(400,'Personal Requests',NULL,NULL,NULL,40,NULL,10,'list burdens & concerns I am praying for:',NULL),(401,'Daily Attitude of my Heart - Sacrifice','If I follow JESUS, I must deny myself and take up my cross daily and follow YOU in a conscience and intentional way.','Luke 9:23',NULL,1,NULL,11,'I present myself as a living sacrifice, FATHER may your love flow to and through me.',NULL),(402,'Daily Attitude of my Heart - Focus','I have been crucified with YOU; & it is no longer I who live, but YOU live in me; & the life which I now live in the flesh I live by faith in YOUR Son, who loved me & gave Himself up for me.','Galatians 2:20',NULL,2,NULL,11,NULL,NULL),(403,'Daily Attitude of my Heart - Obey','Why would I call YOU ‘Lord, Lord,’ and not do what YOU said? As my Lord, I choose to obey YOU today.','Luke 6:46',NULL,3,NULL,11,'I will agree with YOUR truth and take action on that today.',NULL),(404,'Daily Attitude of my Heart - Thoughts','The god of this world has blinded the minds of the unbelieving so that they might not see the light of the gospel of the glory of Christ, who is the image of God.','2 Corinthians 4:4','Take thoughts & feelings captive.',4,NULL,11,'So, it\'s imperative that we have \"on\" a godly attitude each day. If we are cleansed & prepared vessels, then we will be ready & available for whatever it is that YOU might call me to do next.',NULL),(405,'My Father in Heaven','And call no man your father on earth, for you have one Father, who is in heaven.','Matthew 23:9 ESV',NULL,5,NULL,11,'Thank YOU for adopting me into YOUR forever family because of my faith in JESUS.',NULL),(406,'I exalt & glorify YOUR holy Name','The name El Shaddai appears seven times in the Word of God. As I read the newspapers, I can go back to the Book of Genesis and see that immutable, unbreakable promise that God made to father Abraham. Genesis 17:1-2 says, \"And when Abram was ninety years old and nine, the LORD appeared to Abram, and said unto him, I am the Almighty God; walk before Me, and be thou perfect. And I will make My covenant between Me and thee, and will multiply thee exceedingly.\" This promise has changed the world. Every Jew upon the face of the earth is a living testimony of the faithfulness of Almighty God. And this God who keeps His promise to Abraham is the same God that keeps His promises to you and I through Jesus Christ.','Genesis 17:1-19, 28:3; 35:11; 43:14; 48:3; Exodus 6:2-3; Ruth 1:20; Job 5:17; Ezekiel 10:5; Psalm 91:1, Genesis 49:24; Psalm 132:2,5',NULL,6,NULL,11,'YOU are: EL SHADDAI [el-shah-dahy]: “God Almighty,” “The Mighty One of Jacob” – speaks to God’s ultimate power over all. All Sufficient ONE, God of the mountains, the Mighty One of Jacob.',NULL),(407,'YOUR Nature','For it is better to suffer for doing good, if that should be YOUR will, than for doing evil.','1 Peter 3:17',NULL,7,NULL,11,'I worship because YOU are: Sovreign',NULL),(408