 will never fail or forsake me ever.',NULL),(526,'I exalt & glorify YOUR holy Name','(Nehemiah 9:17; Psalm 139:19) -El appears to mean “power,” as in “I have the power to harm you” (Genesis 31:29). El is associated with other qualities, such as integrity (Numbers 23:19), jealousy (Deuteronomy 5:9), and compassion (Nehemiah 9:31), but the root idea of “might” remains. YOU have the power to do anything in my life. If i am stuck in a spot then it is either because of a lack of obedience on my part or because YOU know it is best for me for the moment in order to learn. For my part, may I let no disobedience remain so YOU are free to move on my behalf when YOU deem best.','Neh 9:17',NULL,6,NULL,14,'YOU are: EL, ELOAH [el, el-oh-ah]: God \"mighty, strong, prominent\"',NULL),(527,'YOUR Nature','YOUR law is perfect, reviving my soul; YOUR testimony is sure, making my simple mind wise; YOUR precepts are right, filling my heart with rejoicing; YOUR commandment is pure, enlightening my eyes; YOUR fear is clean, enduring forever; YOUR rules are true, & righteous altogether.','Psalms 19:7-9',NULL,7,NULL,14,'I worship because YOU are: Truth',NULL),(528,'Scripture reading',NULL,'Psalms',NULL,8,NULL,14,'Read 1 Chapter in the Psalms',NULL),(529,'Yeild to YOU','YOUR Kingdom come (act of waiting & longing for my real home), YOUR will, (timing & desire) be done on earth & in my life as it is in Heaven.','Mat 6:10',NULL,9,NULL,14,'There is no eternal point in my efforts unless YOU are doing the work. My best ideas are as filthy rags!',NULL),(530,'Wait on YOU','YOU wait to be gracious to me, and therefore YOU exalt YOURself to show mercy to me. Lord YOU are a God of justice; blessed are all those who wait for YOU.','‭‭Isaiah‬ ‭30:18‬',NULL,10,NULL,14,'I am waiting & consciously pausing so YOU can take the lead today.',NULL),(531,'Recognize my sin & idoltry','But my iniquities have made a separation between me and YOU, and my sins have hidden YOUR face from me so that YOU will not hear.',